reviews.text: This restaurant is always consistent. Great service and food. The thin crust and cheese blanket are a necessity! Pretzel bites are delicious too. They also have daily specials.

Here me out; I NEVER write reviews using half eaten/reheated/paper-plate-photographed food... but this, THIS pizza deserves a heartfelt no-matter-the-physical-documentation-available review.

(I do apologize for not photographing sooner in the consuming process, but to be honest, I didn't have unrealistically high expectations for this particular pizza joint. The existing reviews were "so-so," and the menu didn't depict anything truly special. Clearly, I was misled.)

We ordered this pizza today purely out of convenience, not realizing it was going to be some of the best local-to-Tennessee-pizza we'd ever eat. I've been gluten-free (by choice, not celiac) for 4 years now, and typically, pizza is an extremely underwhelming experience for me, so I didn't expect much else this time.

Surprisingly, not only did their cauliflower crust have an actual appealing flavor (üôå) it was perfectly stacked with FLAVORFUL toppings and mounded with the perfect amount of cheese (for cheese lovers, like ME) to make it an acceptable "REAL" pizza!

(I think it was called "The Hoss"?. *Pepperoni, Italian sausage (which had an amazing flavor and I highly recommend!!), and extra cheese. Then I added onions... because'duh'.)

It was a lovely UNEXPECTED surprise, and I wish we would have taken a chance on them much sooner than we did.

üçï
The half bacon-feta salad is inexpensive, huge and made with very fresh ingredients. The bruschetta flatbread was so delicious!

The bread is good, has a nice Brady flavor to it. The sauce has a nice fresh tomatoey flavor to it not too strong not to acidy just a little sweetness. Pepperoni is good but honestly it was a little sparse could use a little more pepperoni per serving. Now down to the cheese this place clearly caters to cheese lovers I just got extra cheese and it's literally so thick and pulling off the slices. If you are a cheese lover definitely get the extra cheese or what they call the cheese blanket but if you just want to be able to taste the rest of the pizza I suggest do not get extra cheese stick with the regular amount and you'll be able to taste all the fine toppings as well as the bread. The service was very nice and everyone was cordial and polite. Reasonably priced would definitely eat here again.

I ordered a 16pc hot wing with bone in thinking I'd get traditional fried wings covered in hot sauce. I got the driest naked unsauced wings ever and 1 ranch for a 16pc. I thought it was a joke and they put the sauce on the side but nope, that was marinara. They don't even seem fried wth. They look and taste disgusting. I'm not from Tennessee, so honestly I thought maybe this is a Tennessee thing. I even went and asked the worker if they're supposed to be like this.
